Ok I'll give a fair review...

The Place is clean and hygienic.
The bathroom and toilet are clean.
They have a dormitory, halls, and rooms (ac and nonac).
Prices for nonac dormitories are 100 INR per day.
You'll get a dormitory bed for sure no need to worry.
No drinking water facility though, you have to buy  RO water for 5 INR per 2 litres.
You'll get food in the premises for 60 INR per plate.
Beware of monkeys if you are leaving your luggage in the rooms or dorms, lock all the doors and windows before leaving.
No locker facilities available.

Transport:
Take the electric bus from the new mathura bus stand to pagal baba mandir(Mathura - vrindavan route).
It's walking distance from there.

Best place to stay for budget travelers.
10rs ride to Annapurna sewa sansthan where you'll get free lunch if you're from another district or State.
